headline: CrowdStrike earnings, auto sales, Fed's Powell: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Allie Canal previews several of the biggest stories to come tomorrow, Tuesday, December 2, including earnings results from CrowdStrike Holdings (CRWD), Okta (OKTA), and American Eagle Outfitters (AEO); the latest reading on US auto sales; and commentary from Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell on Monday, followed by Fed Vice Chair for Supervision Michelle Bowman testifying before Congress tomorrow. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.
